headline: Landus Cooperative hires former Bunge executive as its new CEO
summary: Landus Cooperative hired Eric Heismeyer, a former Bunge executive, as its new CEO. He replaces Matt Carstens, who stepped down abruptly in April.

headline: Landus Appoints Eric Heismeyer as the Cooperative's Next CEO
summary: Landus, Iowa's largest farmer-owned cooperative, announced today that Eric Heismeyer will join the organization as Chief Executive Officer, effective September 3, 2025. His appointment reaffirms Landus and the Board of Directors' commitment to finding a forward-thinking, proven leader who understands the key role cooperatives play in supporting Iowa farms and rural communities.
